 Figure 6: Google’s TPUv3 Pod, consisting of 1024 TPUv3 chips w/peak performance of >100 petaflop/s   Low Precision Numeric Formats for Machine Learning   TPUv2 and TPUv3 use a custom-designed floating point format called bfloat16 [Wang and Kanwar 2019],  which departs from the IEEE half-precision 16-bit format to provide a format that is more useful for  machine learning and also enables much cheaper multiplier circuits.
